               <msContents>
                  <summary/>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i0">
                     <locus from="1r" to="222v">1r-222v</locus>
                     <textLang xml:lang="ar">Arabic</textLang>
                     <title type="acephalous apodous lacunous" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT0049IHA">قران</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="ar">
                        <locus target="#3r">-3r</locus>والمحصنات من النساء الا ما ملكت ايمانكم كتب الله عليكم واحل لكم ما وراء [ذلكم] ان تبتغوا باموالكم<note>Printed page number: 85.</note>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="ar">
                        <locus target="#222v">-222v</locus>شاهدا مبشرا ونذيرا . لتؤمنوا بالله</explicit>
                     <note>Lithographic print on acidic paper that has become brittle. No printing information remains. Contains verses 3:30-48:9 (lacunous). Printed page numbers, several errors in numbering. Fols 1-2 consist of crumbled pages. Fol. 3 is loose and consists of pages 85-86 and contains verses from sura 4. Fol. 4r is page 55 and begins with the latter part of verse 3:30. The text ends on fol. 222v with the first two words of verse 48:9. Printed floral frames on fols 106v-107r and 147v-148r. Crumbled remains of pages between the pages. Fol. 222 survives only partly. Vocalized.</note>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
